investigating and deterring human rights abuses by the South African Police Services: South African 
Police Service Act (1995). The creation of the ICD was one part of a set of policing reforms which 
aimed to prevent human rights violations by the police and to improve police-community relations. 
See also the National Crime Prevention Strategy (1996) and the National Crime Combating Strategy 
(2000). See further David Bruce and Rachel Neild, <i>The Police We Want: A Handbook for Oversight 
of the Police in South Africa</i> (2005); David Bruce, Gareth Newham and Themba Masuku, <i>In Service 
of the People&#8217;s Democracy: An Assessment of the South African Police Service </i>(2007). 
</p>
<p> 91 Bronwen Manby, &#8220;The South African Independent Complaints Directorate&#8221; in Andrew Goldsmith 
and Colleen Lewis, <i>Civilian Oversight of Policing: Governance, Democracy and Human Rights</i> 
